INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

Welcome to our Warsaw Impact Community!

We‚Äôre growing fast, and we‚Äôre excited to have you here. Whether you‚Äôre a passionate crowd member, an art lover who wants to connect with the artists you see on stage, or a creative looking to network, this is your place.

If you‚Äôre an aspiring artist thinking about how to earn money from your craft and take the leap into becoming a full-time creative, you‚Äôll find support, ideas, and inspiration here. This community is all about connection, creativity, and growth.

Together we learn, share, and improve as artists through exclusive workshops, meetups, live shows, festivals, and more, crucially, we‚Äôre building a space where the right people can discover you. Actors, musicians, and performers in our community are regularly seen by casting agents, talent scouts, and industry professionals who come to our events looking for fresh talent. If you want exposure, meaningful industry connections, and a real chance to be discovered, this is the place to be.

We‚Äôre glad you‚Äôve joined us, get ready to perform, connect, and be seen.

items.text:
INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

üé≠ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì New Australian Play in London** üé≠

We are casting **four roles** for an exciting new Australian play, *The Beat of the Bronzewing*, which will have a **showcase reading at the Hen & Chickens Theatre, Islington, on November 12th**.

üå™Ô∏è **About the Play:**
When Peggy shows up at Lorraine‚Äôs shack in dead-end tropical Australia, she brings an irresistible offer: a one-way ticket out of there. But with a cyclone looming and old wounds resurfacing, can Lorraine be convinced she has nothing to lose?

‚ú® Longlisted for the **Theatre 503 International Playwriting Award 2025**, *The Beat of the Bronzewing* explores the lives of three women in remote Australia, grappling with toxic femininity, domestic abuse, and rural isolation. Set against an evocative tropical landscape, the play is a gripping story of friendship, fear, and survival.

üë©‚Äçüé§ **The Team**

üì¢Volunteers Wanted - Videographers! Liverpool Mystery Eventüì¢

CAJ Productions is looking for 2 more reliable volunteers to help with a one-off mystery stunt in Liverpool City Centre on Saturday 20th September 2025.

It's part of a brand-new UK theatre tour coming in 2026, and this will be one of our headline public marketing stunts. 

The role is simple, but really important:

. Filming the event (reactions) on a phone (2 people required)

What you'll get:

. Travel expenses covered

. Be part of an unusual, exciting event that's going to get a lot of attention

. Something different to talk about (and looks great on a CV for anyone in events, film, or theatre)

If you're free, reliable, and up for being part of something mysterious and fun, drop me a message here or comment below and I'll share the details.

Thanks! 

Charlie

CASTING CALL

We‚Äôre looking for a female actor to join us this December for our RAPUNZEL pantomime (school tour). 

We‚Äôre casting either of the following parts, with our existing performer playing the opposite role. 

- Rapunzel (lead)
- Gothel (villain)

Last year was our best selling tour - but we hope to beat that this year! Because it‚Äôs schools, the shows are weekday mornings and early afternoons, so you‚Äôll have your evenings and weekends free. The performances are in the Norfolk, Suffolk and Cambridge area. 

We‚Äôre currently offering a minimum of ¬£870 - which will go up as we get more bookings in + travel expenses. 
The tour spans from 1st - 19th December 2025. 
Aiming to start weekly rehearsals asap - in Hunstanton (PE36). These are unpaid but we keep them as flexible as possible.

This will be our thirteenth panto tour, and we‚Äôve built up a good name in the area, with schools booking us year after year (even before we announce the title!) We pride ourselves on being a warm, friendly, but professional company.

If interested, please get in touch for further details - either by a PM on here, or via email - purple-dreams@hotmail.co.uk - I‚Äôm looking forward to hearing from (some of) you üôÇ

Many thanks
Tobias Nicholls
Creative Director 
Purple Dreams Productions

items.text:
Rainhill Garrick Society are performing ‚Äò Habeus Corpus‚Äô by Alan Bennett on February 12th-14th 2026.

Alan Bennett‚Äôs Habeus Corpus is set some time in the Seventies and follows the lives of the Wicksteed family. The story follows Dr and Muriel Wicksteed as they both seek pleasure and fun outside of their marital relationship. The farcical play is very fast paced, incredibly funny and occasionally surreal. The bumbling sex-obsessed British characters such as the virginal vicar, the Ô¨Çat chested spinster, the peering doctor, his frustrated wife and of course a bra salesman man all come together in this bizarre and thoroughly entertaining story.

Parts available:-

Dennis Wicksteed - the hypochondriac son of Dr Wickseed, (20-30)

Felicity Rumpers - young, nubile, upper class  (20-30)

Constance Wicksteed - the sister of Dr Wicksteed, flat chested and sex starved, (20+) 

Play read through Tuesday 21st October at 7.30 in Rainhill Village Hall
Auditions- Thursday 23rd October at 7.30 Rainhill Village Hall 
Rehearsals are on Tuesdays and Thursday evenings 7.30-9.30 and the 3 Sundays prior to the performance.
Audition pieces are available on request. 

We are an amateur group so the roles are unpaid, but we are a well respected group of 83 years standing who enjoy great support from a large dedicated audience. 
The play is great fun with some slapstick and music but with some poignant moments that say a lot about relationships.

For further information contact: sophiebrogan99@gmail.com

items.text:
Hey everyone my name is Manraj Heer I‚Äôm the producer for our student short film at Vancouver Film School. The film is called ‚ÄúBeginnings‚Äù and we are shooting on October 11th & 12th, 2025. We are currently looking to hire three male actors. For the roles of Athan, Hooded Man, and Rick. If you are interested please send your resume, headshot, and any demo reel to teambeginnings@gmail.com and we will reach out to you for a self tape to help narrow down the process.

The deadline for demo tapes and applications end on October 3rd, 2025. So please get in your application at your earliest convenience.

Synopsis:
Athan celebrates his 21st birthday surrounded by the people he loves the most. Family and
friends cheer for the start of a new phase of Athan‚Äôs life. A new beginning. Until time suddenly
stops. Everyone freezing in place, except for Athan, who knows the memory has ended.
Guided by a Hooded Man, an older and wiser version of himself, Athan must find purpose by
visiting rooms in a seemingly never-ending hallway, each filled with crucial moments of his life
‚Äî learning the role of the people that surround him (and the impact he has on them), dealing
with love in an ever-transforming relationship, and embracing grief from the never-stopping
passage of time.
After impulsively deciding to skip entering the rest of the doors out of agony, Athan will find
how quickly a lifetime goes by ‚Äî but be ready to accept his new chapter behind a final, bright room.

CASTING BREAKDOWN ‚Äì VANCOUVER FILM SCHOOL
Project Title: Beginnings
Project Type: Student Short Film
Union Status: Non-Union
Director: J. D. Estevez
Producer: Raj Heer / Vancouver Film School
Casting Director: Manraj Heer, J. D. Estevez
Audition Dates: Self-tapes due by October 3rd, 2025
Audition Location: Self-tapes only
Call Back Dates: October 4th, 2025
Call Back Location: 142 Water Street, Vancouver, BC V6B 1B2
Shooting Dates: October 11th ‚Äì 12th, 2025
Shooting Location: Greater Vancouver Area
Rates: Unpaid. Catering and craft service provided.
Submission Instructions: Please submit resume, headshot, and demo reel
to teambeginnings@gmail.com and indicate which role you‚Äôd like to be considered for.

ATHAN / MALE / AGE : 20-25 / ANY ETHNICITY 

Na√Øve and foolish, Athan thinks he knows what he wants from life and what it is to be expected of him ‚Äî learning soon enough that you can never be prepared for what is behind
the next door. Though he is slow to realize the importance of every moment, and too clumsy
to show it, Athan is a deeply caring and empathetic person. He is willing to push everything
out of his way to spend more time with someone he loves. Despite repeatedly stumbling
through the hallway of life, Athan is motivated by a constant search for meaning.

HOODED MAN / MALE / AGE : 50-60 / ANY ETHNICITY
After living as a rebellious young Athan, the Hooded Man walks through the hallway of his life
once again. This time, he reflects on his past, accepting it for what it is, knowing he cannot
change it. Melancholic and somewhat regretful, he guides Athan, emphasizing the
importance of embracing every stage of life, whether joyful or somber. Unlike his younger
self, the Hooded Man moves deliberately through every memory, without hurry, but with
peace. Though seemingly stoic, there is a hint of disturbance behind his expression.

RICK / MALE / AGE : 40-50 / ANY ETHNICITY
Athan‚Äôs father, Rick, is a troubled man. He learned from his family to hide his true feelings and
often relies on bad habits to forget his past mistakes. He was able to distance himself from his
vices when he found a sense of purpose, such as when he married his childhood friend,
Emma. However, it didn't last long. Overwhelmed by regret and fearing that he won‚Äôt make
the most of his life, Rick sees Athan as a chance to start over. He is determined to ensure that
his son won't make the same mistakes he did. However, with his marriage falling apart and
Athan soon becoming independent, Rick can‚Äôt help but start drinking again.

 Look forward to seeing everyone‚Äôs submissions! If you have any questions or concerns please reach me at teambeginnings@gmail.com.

items.text:
**Hola Everyone,**

I‚Äôm a SAG-AFTRA actor, director, and coach with 25+ years in this business. You might‚Äôve seen me in *Cry Macho*, *Minority Report*, *War of the Worlds*, *American Horror Story*, *Sons of Anarchy*, *NCIS: LA*, or as Marc Molina on *The Secret Life of the American Teenager*. My voice has also popped up in games like *Red Dead Redemption II* and *L.A. Noire*.

I‚Äôve taught at Theatre of Arts Hollywood, Scott Sedita Acting Studios, my own JLP Acting Company, and as a teaching artist with nonprofit organizations.

I just opened enrollment for *Art of Acting Online: Foundations* ‚Äî a 4-week course where we dig into script analysis, voice & speech, self-taping, live Zoom auditions, and most importantly, connecting the craft to who you are as an artist.

If you‚Äôre ready to sharpen your craft and ground your auditions, check it out here:
[https://preview.mailerlite.io/preview/136905/emails/164574496055887710](https://preview.mailerlite.io/preview/136905/emails/164574496055887710)

Familiar Faces Casting Call Short Fim Directed by: Daniela Aguirre DATE POSTED: 09-22-2025 POSSIBLE SHOOTING DATES: November 8th OR November 9th, 2025 Rehearsal dates: TBD Location: Chicago, IL
We are committed to diverse, inclusive casting. For every role, please submit qualifiec performers, without regard to disability, race, age, color, national origin, ethnic origin, sexua orientation, gender identity, or any other basis prohibited by law unless otherwise specifically indicated.
Logline : A college undergrad soaring to become a pediatric speech therapist is taunted by ar unexplainable nightmare that has gradually become worse over time.
Roles:
Katalina Desdemona (22) ( Portrayed female Lead) - A senior year college undergrad who grew up in an abusive houschold that impacted her by severely delaying her speech development. With ome help from her ELD teacher (English Language Development) Katalina was able to express herself more growing up and dreams of doing the same for others,
Young Katalina (7-9) (Portrayed female- lead)- Evil spirit who imitates the appearance o Katalina when she was younger. Who's seeking to collect her promised teeth.
Pierre Baker (22) (Portrayed male- supporting)- The loyal best friend of Katalina since 5" grade and who also took interest in studying for child development and literacy. Dedicated and nurturing best friend
If interested, available, or have questions email Daniela Aguirre Send headshots, resumes/reels 

to email: daguirre2@colum.edu

Deadline Date: October 24th. 2025
Compensation: Meal, Copy, Credit

S√òGER AKUT SKUESPILLER, KVINDE 65+ 

Grundet sygdom er vores skuespiller i morgen desv√¶rre hoppet fra, s√• vi s√∏ger akut en Kvinde p√• 65+ der kunne have lyst til at v√¶re med. Projektet er desv√¶rre ul√∏nnet, men der er forplejning og god stemning p√• set. 

Lokation: Spring forbi strandpark 
Tidsrum: Dagstimerne
‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
Tidligere opslag: 

Vi er et ungt hold af filmskabere, som s√∏ger en kvindelig skuespiller, der kunne have lyst til at arbejde sammen med os et par dage, n√•r vi optager vores kortfilm ‚ÄúEventyret om Fr√∏prinsen‚Äù d. 19-21. og 26-28. September. Rollen er ikke l√∏nnet da det er et lidt mindre projekt, som er finansieret ud af egen lomme.

Historien:

Et moderne og f√∏lsomt ungdomseventyr om 12-√•rige Matilde, en ensom pige med store dr√∏mme om √¶gte k√¶rlighed. En dag ser hun en dreng gennem en h√¶k, som idyllisk sidder og skriver i sin have. Noget ved ham fanger hende. Mathilde bygger en smuk fantasi op omkring ham, som hun bliver besat af.

Hun m√• i kontakt med ham. Men det er ikke let, n√•r fantasien og virkeligheden skal m√∏des, slet ikke n√•r drengens bedstemor, som han bor hos, ikke ligefrem er typen der tror p√• k√¶rlighed ved f√∏rste blik.

En smuk og melankolsk fort√¶lling om l√¶ngsel, dr√∏mme og den f√∏rste k√¶rlighed. Et twist p√• det klassiske fr√∏prins eventyr.

Bedstemoderen:

Sigrid repr√¶senterer et mere pragmatisk syn p√• k√¶rlighed og giver ikke meget for den medrivende forelskelse, som Matilde v√¶gter s√• h√∏jt. Hun finder den upassende og derfor er hun ikke interesseret i, at de to unge mennesker skal m√∏des

Et moderne og f√∏lsomt ungdomseventyr om 12-√•rige Matilde, en ensom pige med store dr√∏mme om √¶gte k√¶rlighed. En dag ser hun en dreng gennem en h√¶k, som idyllisk sidder og skriver i sin have. Noget ved ham fanger hende. Mathilde bygger en smuk fantasi op omkring ham, som hun bliver besat af.

Hun m√• i kontakt med ham. Men det er ikke let, n√•r fantasien og virkeligheden skal m√∏des, slet ikke n√•r drengens bedstemor, som han bor hos, ikke ligefrem er typen der tror p√• k√¶rlighed ved f√∏rste blik.

En smuk og melankolsk fort√¶lling om l√¶ngsel, dr√∏mme og den f√∏rste k√¶rlighed. Et twist p√• det klassiske fr√∏prins eventyr.

Bedstemoderen:

Sigrid repr√¶senterer et mere pragmatisk syn p√• k√¶rlighed og giver ikke meget for den medrivende forelskelse, som Matilde v√¶gter s√• h√∏jt. Hun finder den upassende og derfor er hun ikke interesseret i, at de to unge mennesker skal m√∏des

items.text:
The first 10 mins of my first full length play Blackout 1985 is going to be performed as part of Wooden Arrow Productions next scratch evening on 30th October at Lamda at their Sainsburys Theatre!

The casting is UNPAID but there will be professional photography, industry guests for feedback and a chance to network after with the guests and the audience. There are also other roles in other plays that need filling. 

Deadline is this Saturday!

Synopsis of Blackout 1985: 28th September 1985. A day marked in history. The Lewis family gathers in their living room as the streets outside erupt in flames. Winston and Angie strive to protect their children, Jimmy and Asha, from a world that denies their humanity. As generational wounds, dreams, and tensions collide, the family must decide whether to stay safe behind closed doors or step into the fire of history. Blackout 1985 is the first in the trilogy, which shines a light on key Black British moments.

If you are interested or know anyone please go to this link - 
https://forms.gle/uJFMiQzyR6kVqBae8

Kind regards,
Angela Boehm Casting Team

Movietime September 2025, The Third

EINE WARMHERZIGE STORY ≈∞BER BR√úDER UND EIN NEUES MAGISCHES SCHULJAHR STARTET

Die zweite Septemberh√§lfte bringt nicht nur Leonardo Di Caprio zur√ºck ins Kino (Stadtkino Center Laa), sondern es beginnt ein neues Jahr mit der SCHULE DER MAGISCHEN TIERE 4 (Babylon Kino, Filmb√ºhne Waidhofen/Ybbs).

Einem ungleichen Br√ºderpaar begegnet man in GANZER HALBER BRUDER (Stadtkino Horn), wobei wir mit dem Hauptdarsteller Christoph Maria Herbst ein paar Worte plaudern durften.

Der √ñ Film hat weitere Highlights parat, wo wir in der Sendung auch 2 Interviews mit den RegisseurInnen f√ºhren konnten. NARBEN EINES PUTSCHES oder HOW TO BE NORMAL AND THE ODDNESS OF THE OTHER WORLD (Kronenkino Mistelbach).

In den Lichtspielen Gf√∂hl gibt es Ende September einen besonderen Event mit dem Filmarchiv Austria und wir trafen eine Zeitzeugin, die im Sitzendorfer Kino noch die Sissi-Filme gesehen hat.

Abgerundet wird das Kinomagazin musikalisch in Memoriam Robert Redford, in dem wir Songs und Themes seiner besten Filme pr√§sentieren.

Mittwoch 24.09.2025 von 17 bis 19h EXKLUSIV auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

Casting Call - Vancouver BC

Non-Union

Shoot Dates: October (TBD)

Rate: $200 (one day shoot)

Location: Vancouver BC, Kerrisdale.

ROLE:

[Male Lead]

Age: 27-38

Ethnicity: Any

Gender: Man

Callbacks and Rehearsal: Zoom. 

Tone: Grounded and realistic. (e.g Normal People on Prime)

We are seeking a male lead for a one-day location shoot in Kerrisdale for our proof of concept short film. The actor should be comfortable with intimate conversations and improv; open to collaborating during rehearsal to complete the script as we are looking for a very natural and realistic dialogue. 

 TO SUBMIT and RECEIVE AUDITION SIDES: Please send your name, contact info, recent photos or headshots and availability to: [mariajulianakidmoro@gmail.com]

Thanks! Maria and Gabi.

Callbacks and Rehearsal: Zoom. 

Tone: Grounded and realistic. (e.g Normal People on Prime)

We are seeking a male lead for a one-day location shoot in Kerrisdale for our proof of concept short film. The actor should be comfortable with intimate conversations and improv; open to collaborating during rehearsal to complete the script as we are looking for a very natural and realistic dialogue. 

 TO SUBMIT and RECEIVE AUDITION SIDES: Please send your name, contact info, recent photos or headshots and availability to: [mariajulianakidmoro@gmail.com]

Thanks! Maria and Gabi.

items.text:
Hej allesammen

Vi er et par elever fra KBH Film- og Fotoskole, der er i gang med vores midtvejs projekt. 

Vi har skrevet en ca. 12-min lang kortfilm, hvori en ung mand ikke n√•r sit S-tog fra K√∏ge Nord st, fordi han bliver blokeret af en hund. I den forbindelse vil vi h√∏re, om der er nogen som kunne have lyst til at l√•ne deres vuffer (og dem selv) til nogle unge ambiti√∏se filmskabere i ca. 1 time. 

Vi leder efter en mellemstor hund -- race er underordnet. Den skal helst kunne finde ud af at holde fokus p√• et enkelt menneske, sitte, og kunne hoppe op ad en person. 

Hvor og hvorn√•r?

Vi filmer allerede tirsdag d. 30 september kl. 19-20. Optagelserne foreg√•r p√• K√∏ge Nord st. Vi d√¶kker for forplejninger p√• set, og transport

Vigtig info
* I den endeligt klippet film vil det fremg√•, at hunden bliver skubbet af en person. Dette er et stunt vi naturligvis vil skabe udelukkende med kameratricks, og hunden vil ikke rent faktisk blive skubbet
* Vi vil selvf√∏lgelig gerne have ejeren med p√• set, s√• hunden f√∏ler sig tryggest

Hvis dig og din hund kunne v√¶re interesseret, s√• skriv en privat besked, eller en mail til vores instrukt√∏r Dizzie p√• dizzie.saugmann@gmail.com, med kontakt info, et vellignende billede af vovseren, og gerne lidt om dens personlighed.

P√• foreh√•nd tak!

items.text:
The first 10 mins of my first full length play Blackout 1985 is going to be performed as part of Wooden Arrow Productions next scratch evening on 30th October at Lamda at their Sainsburys Theatre!

The casting is UNPAID but there will be professional photography, industry guests for feedback and a chance to network after with the guests and the audience. There are also other roles in other plays that need filling. 

Deadline is this Saturday!

Synopsis of Blackout 1985: 28th September 1985. A day marked in history. The Lewis family gathers in their living room as the streets outside erupt in flames. Winston and Angie strive to protect their children, Jimmy and Asha, from a world that denies their humanity. As generational wounds, dreams, and tensions collide, the family must decide whether to stay safe behind closed doors or step into the fire of history. Blackout 1985 is the first in the trilogy, which shines a light on key Black British moments.

If you are interested or know anyone please go to this link - https://forms.gle/uJFMiQzyR6kVqBae8

Competitive salary, flights and accommodation provided.

Hello, Nice to meet you. 

I'm Yoshikazu Saito, a Tokyo-based actor currently producing a film. And for this project, I'd like to show the story of a man born in japan and adopted in United States. It is Japanese cinema but, to challenge norms, in Japanglish. I mean in Japanese-English.

Currently, we need more financial support to develop the film. With your donate of our film, we could continue with our concept, showing that we have our ways of owning universal languages.

Below is a link to our PayPal, open for your support for our vision. And please share the proposal with your friends. 

Our team will also appreciate if you will share it with your friends as well.

Thank you very much and I wish you have a great day.

**CASTING CALL TIL KORTFILM P√Ö KBHFF **

Hej alle,

Vi s√∏ger 3 skuespillere til et midtvejsprojekt "Noget for Nogen" p√• K√∏benhavns Film og Foto skole. 

"Noget for Nogen" er et trekantsdrama sat inden for rammerne af en romantisk horror. Et k√¶restepar lader en fremmed kvinde overnatte i deres nye hus, men fra f√∏rste √∏jeblik bliver parret spillet ud mod hinanden, alt imens aftenen tager en mere og mere okkult drejning. Overlever parforholdet til en ny dag?

**ROLLER:**

**SOSJA** (20'erne - 30'erne) - HOVEDKARAKTER

Sosjas st√∏rste √∏nske at v√¶re mor og k√¶mper for at f√• sin k√¶reste til at dele hendes dr√∏m. Hun finder stor mening i at v√¶re noget for nogen. 

**JAKE** (20'erne - 30'erne) - Sosjas k√¶reste

Har et stort behov for at finde sig selv og sin hylde i livet. Han er arbejdsl√∏s og lyver om at v√¶re steril, for at undg√• at f√• b√∏rn. 

**LUCY** (20'erne - 30'erne) - Den fremmede g√¶st

Vil gerne friste og manipulere Sosja og Jakes forhold, for at se hvor langt hun kan presse dem og i sidste ende √∏del√¶gge deres forhold. Hun er en repr√¶sentation af dj√¶velen og det okkulte element. 

Skriv en PB eller send en mail til nogetfornogenfilm@gmail.com, hvis det v√¶kker interesse

Vi h√•ber I vil v√¶re med, og vi gl√¶der os til at h√∏re fra jer!

Bh,

William, Mathias, Marius og Benjamin

Please get the Word Out that Jodi Purdy is looking for 3 Generations from Rhode Island - Grampa, his Son and his Grandson for a Commercial for a Medical Company.  

This pays $500 per person for one day on set with a professional crew and award-winning Director.

I just cast 16 actors in one of my clients Commercials in Austin Texas! Surely, I can find 3 in Rhode Island!

The boy has to live in Rhode Island.  So a boy between 6 and 9 and his dad would be great! I can find an actor to play the Grampa!!

Help a girl out and share if you live in RI!! 

I don‚Äôt want to have to go to RI!  

But I will, I‚Äôll have a good Olde Fashion Casting Call! Remember those??

## Dramatic Improv Workshops from Theatre Momentum! We're proud to present:
# **Get in Focus - An Online Subversive's Workshop** with David Razowsky
# Sundays, October 5-26 ¬∑ 12-3 PM Central

What are you focused on when you begin a scene? What great offers are you missing because you‚Äôre building a story instead of connecting to your emotional responses? This four-week online workshop will teach you how to use the power of kinesthetic responses to immediately build strong scenes, recognize what your body is already telling you, and then build a great connection from there.

This is an excellent primer for those who‚Äôve never studied with Dave.

**Sundays, October 5-26, 12-3 PM Central [VIA ZOOM]**

https://www.theatremomentum.com/guest-classes
